<h1 align="center">📊 Feature Scaling and Learning Rate</h1>
<h3 align="center">Machine Learning Optimization Experiment</h3>

<p align="center">
This project demonstrates the importance of 
<b>feature scaling</b> and <b>learning rate selection</b> 
in machine learning optimization using Gradient Descent.
</p>

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

Improper feature scaling and incorrect learning rate values can severely affect model training:

- Slow convergence  
- Unstable optimization  
- Poor performance  

This notebook explores:

- Gradient Descent behavior  
- Impact of feature scaling  
- Learning rate tuning  
- Cost convergence visualization  

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

```
Feature_Scaling_and_Learning_Rate.ipynb
README.md
```

---

## 🧠 Concepts Covered

- Gradient Descent Algorithm  
- Feature Scaling (Normalization / Standardization)  
- Learning Rate Optimization  
- Cost Function Minimization  
- Convergence Analysis  

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used

- Python  
- NumPy  
- Matplotlib  
- Jupyter Notebook  

---

## 📈 Experiments Included

### 1️⃣ Without Feature Scaling
- Slow convergence  
- Oscillating cost values  
- Inefficient parameter updates  

### 2️⃣ With Feature Scaling
- Faster convergence  
- Smooth cost reduction  
- Stable training  

### 3️⃣ Learning Rate Experiments
- Small learning rate → Slow training  
- Optimal learning rate → Fast convergence  
- Large learning rate → Divergence  

---

## 🖥️ How to Run the Project

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
```

Launch Jupyter Notebook:

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

Open:

```
Feature_Scaling_and_Learning_Rate.ipynb
```

